# ImGui Test Engine regression tests (precondition verification)

When you add in-process UI tests with **Dear ImGui Test Engine** (or similar hooks that set app state then trigger an action), ensure **state matches what you intended** before triggering the action. Otherwise a test can pass or fail for the wrong reason.

## Rule

After each `Set*` (or equivalent) that affects the next UI action or backend call, **assert the corresponding getter matches** what was set, then trigger the action (search, click sequence, etc.).

## Pattern

- After `SetFoo(value)`, use `IM_CHECK(GetFoo() == value)` (or project assertion macro) before `TriggerBar()`.
- For window-based checks, prefer **exact window title** comparison when the test engine exposes window names.
- For optional controls, **pre-check** visibility (e.g. `ItemExists`) and skip if the control is absent in that build.

## MindMap Helper

This repository does not ship ImGui Test Engine by default. When you integrate it (optional; macOS is the usual first target), place regression sources under `src/ui/` with names matching the globs above and apply this discipline.

**Reference:** AGENTS.md — ImGui Test Engine; upstream: https://github.com/ocornut/imgui_test_engine
